text.tspan: MCP4921 is a 12bit DACs (Slaves) are connected with Arduino (Master) via SPI protocol
Arduino has a builtin SPI library that will take care
of the details of sending data when properly set
up and the data has been formatted according to
- chip select line (CS, any unused digital pin, e.g. 3)
When data is to be written to a slave, the CS line of
that chip has to be pulled low [digitalWrite(pin, LOW)],
and back HIGH when the transfer is done.
Vref is the reference voltage and can be connected to
the supply voltage. The DAC maps the 4096 values
to the range of 0.04V to Vdd-0.04V.
